--- body ---
## Context

`@tbl-traditions` in `deliverables/manuscript/manuscript.qmd` (section
"Before climate finance: three disjoint traditions") has a column
"Co-citation anchors (pre-2007)" listing, per tradition, the papers the
table caption calls "the most-connected papers in the algorithmically
detected community". This phrase is a placeholder — it doesn't say what
"most-connected" means (degree? PageRank? betweenness?) or how the
"algorithmically detected community" was built (network construction,
detection algorithm, resolution/seed parameters, how detected communities
were matched to the three named traditions).

Under this project's provenance norm (cite only pipeline numbers
traceable to an archived output — `feedback_manuscript_number_provenance.md`),
the caption and the methodological appendix both need to name the actual
metric and procedure the analysis code computed, not a vague gloss.

This ticket was spun off during a manuscript restructuring pass (2026-07-16)
rather than resolved inline, because closing it requires reading the
analysis code/output, not just editing prose.

## Relevant files

- `deliverables/manuscript/manuscript.qmd` — `@tbl-traditions` and its
  caption (search `tbl-traditions`); appendix section A.5 "Second question:
  the citation lineages" is the likely home for the fuller explanation
- the analysis script(s) that produced the pre-2007 co-citation communities
  and their anchor works (not yet identified — first action below)

## Actions

1. Find the script/notebook that computes the pre-2007 co-citation
   communities and anchor works feeding `@tbl-traditions`.
2. Confirm the exact anchor-selection metric (e.g. "the three highest-degree
   nodes within each detected community") and the community-detection
   algorithm + parameters used.
3. Update the table caption to name the metric precisely instead of
   "most-connected".
4. Add a short paragraph to appendix A.5 describing network construction
   (nodes, edge/co-citation threshold), the detection algorithm, and how
   detected communities were matched to the three named traditions (if
   manual, say so).
5. Point the appendix paragraph at the producing script / archived output.

## Test

No code test — this is a documentation-accuracy ticket. Verification is
manual: the caption and appendix text must match what the code actually
did (traceability check).

## Verification

- [ ] Caption names the real anchor-selection metric
- [ ] Appendix A.5 describes network construction, algorithm, and
      community-to-tradition matching
- [ ] Both point to the producing script/output

## Invariants

- No change to the analysis code or its outputs — this is a prose/caption
  accuracy fix only.
- `make check` / prose adherence tests continue to pass.

## Exit criteria

- `@tbl-traditions`'s caption and appendix A.5 accurately and specifically
  describe how the co-citation anchors were computed, with no placeholder
  language remaining.
